        <abstract> 
<p>JDH has settled the <hi rend="italic">Leschenaultia</hi> case, but it remains a difficulty to CD.</p>  
<p><hi rend="italic">Goodenia</hi>, like bee orchid, seems a case of a structure with an evident function, which is not carried out. Is curvature of styles an incidental result of growth or a pollination adaptation?</p> 
        </abstract>
