            <note xml:id="foot.f5"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2165.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Samuel Haughton</ref>, professor of geology at Dublin University, had publicly criticised CD’s theory (see <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 7, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-2457.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to J. D. Hooker, 3 May [1859]</ref>). His anonymous review of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_6014.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Origin</hi></ref> was published early in June 1860 ([Haughton] 1860b). See letters to J. D. Hooker, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-2821.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">5 June [1860]</ref>, and to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1957.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Asa Gray</ref>, 8 June [1860].</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f6">Jemmy Button (<ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_779.xml">Orundellico</ref>) was a Fuegian who was brought to England in 1830 by <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1650.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Robert FitzRoy</ref> and returned to Tierra del Fuego on the <hi rend="italic">Beagle</hi> in 1833.</note>
